  "narrative_arc": "Orphan born in a workhouse, sold as an apprentice, runs away to London, recruited by a criminal gang, rescued by a gentleman. Dickens documents the Victorian child welfare system as a pipeline from workhouse to crime — every \"rescue\" just moves Oliver to a different form of exploitation.",
  "why_this_character_matters": "Oliver is the original child systems-navigation story. Dickens wrote it to indict the New Poor Law. Building Oliver's dome with both Victorian and modern systems reveals whether the workhouse-to-crime pipeline still exists (it does — it's now the foster-care-to-prison pipeline).",
